Although there are no direct flights to the UK, there are now options for returning indirectly.
Some commercial flights have now commenced or resumed service from Argyle International Airport in St Vincent. Fly One Caribbean has commenced a flight service to Barbados and American Airlines is now offering a weekly service to Miami.
Air Canada is currently scheduled to resume their service between St Vincent and Toronto on 23 July. Connections from Barbados, Miami or Toronto to the UK are available. Caribbean Airlines may also resume service soon.
From 19 July, British Airways will resume a limited flight schedule from Barbados to London.
You should consult FCO Travel Advice for requirements for entry and onward travel in other countries on your route.
When you return, you must follow the rules for entering the UK.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British High Commission Bridgetown on + 1 246 430 7800.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British High Commission on Facebook and Twitter.
